2 unit(s) Beyond Meat®
¾ cup Basmati Rice
113 g Mirepoix
113 g Mushrooms
28 g Baby Spinach
56 g Green Peas
28 g Crispy Shallots
2 tbsp Tomato Sauce Base
1 unit(s) Beef Broth Concentrate
1 tbsp Cream Sauce Spice Blend
1 tbsp Butter*
½ tbsp Oil*
0.06 tsp Pepper*
0.06 tsp Salt*

Once water is boiling, add rice and 1 tbsp (2 tbsp) butter, then reduce heat to low. Cover and cook until rice is tender and liquid is absorbed, 12-14 min.
Remove from heat. Set aside, still covered.

Heat a large non-stick pan over high heat.
While pan heats, quarter mushrooms.
When hot, add 1/2 tbsp (1 tbsp) oil, then Beyond Meat® patties, peas, mushrooms and mirepoix. Season with salt and pepper. Cook, breaking up patties into smaller pieces, until veggies are soft and Beyond Meat® is crispy, 5-6 min.**

Add Cream Sauce Spice Blend, tomato sauce base and broth concentrate. Stir to coat.
Add 3/4 cup (1 1/2 cups) water. Cook, stirring often, until gravy thickens slightly, 2-3 min.
Add spinach and stir until wilted, 30 sec.

Fluff rice with fork, then stir in half the crispy shallots.
Divide rice between bowls.
Top with Beyond Meat® and gravy mixture.
Sprinkle remaining crispy shallots over top.

If you've opted to get Beyond Meat®, cook it the same way as the beef, breaking up patties into smaller pieces, until crispy, 5-6 min.**